# Quiz App

QuizApp is allows admin to generate quizzes which will select questions from question bank randomly and saves quizzes. The user when he plays gets the random quiz from the quizzes the admin had generated

## View Questions [/getquestions]

### List All Questions [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "id": 1,
                "answer": "b",
                "answer1": "Mumbai",
                "answer2": "Delhi",
                "answer3": "Chennai",
                "answer4": "Bangalore",
                "categoryId": 1,
                "difficultyId": 1,
                "questionName": "What is the capital of India"
            }
        ]

## Create Questions [/setquestions]

### Create a New Question [POST]

You may create your own question using this action. It takes all the parameters in the form and performs POST action

+ Request (application/json)

        {
                "id": 1,
                "answer": "b",
                "answer1": "Mumbai",
                "answer2": "Delhi",
                "answer3": "Chennai",
                "answer4": "Bangalore",
                "categoryId": 1,
                "difficultyId": 1,
                "questionName": "What is the capital of India"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /setquestions

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "answer": "b",
                "answer1": "Mumbai",
                "answer2": "Delhi",
                "answer3": "Chennai",
                "answer4": "Bangalore",
                "categoryId": 1,
                "difficultyId": 1,
                "questionName": "What is the capital of India"
            }
            
